# scoreflow project rules

- Keep changes small, focused, and aligned with the existing repository structure.
- Read nearby files before editing so new code follows local naming, formatting, and organization.
- Prefer clear, maintainable implementations over clever abstractions.
- Add or update tests when behavior changes, and run the relevant checks before finishing.
- Avoid introducing new dependencies unless they are necessary and consistent with the project stack.
- Preserve user-authored changes and avoid unrelated refactors.
